1
00:00:11,145 --> 00:00:13,625
Her name is Song, Sadanun Warakij.

2
00:00:13,705 --> 00:00:16,305
<i>She's one of the company's</i>
<i>top food researchers.</i>

3
00:00:16,385 --> 00:00:17,745
<i>I already told you.</i>

4
00:00:17,825 --> 00:00:20,225
<i>I don’t want a serious relationship.</i>

5
00:00:20,305 --> 00:00:22,785
<i>If you’re catching feelings,</i>
<i>then this ends here.</i>

6
00:00:22,865 --> 00:00:23,985
<i>I like you.</i>

7
00:00:24,065 --> 00:00:27,145
<i>And I'm pretty sure</i>
<i>you feel something for me, too.</i>

8
00:00:27,225 --> 00:00:29,505
<i>So much that</i>
<i>I can already picture our future.</i>

9
00:00:29,585 --> 00:00:32,185
We'll get married
and have twin babies together.

10
00:00:32,264 --> 00:00:34,025
Their names will be Ruean and Rai.

11
00:00:42,745 --> 00:00:44,145
I’m kidding.

12
00:00:44,225 --> 00:00:47,105
Our twins would be named
Nirin and Lila instead.

13
00:00:47,705 --> 00:00:49,145
I searched the names online.

14
00:00:49,225 --> 00:00:50,945
It said they’re very auspicious.

15
00:00:51,025 --> 00:00:53,305
The kids will take great care
of parents like us.

16
00:00:53,385 --> 00:00:54,745
Are you insane or something?

17
00:00:55,745 --> 00:00:58,105
How are you imagining that far ahead?

18
00:00:58,185 --> 00:01:00,465
-I don’t--
-I know you’re not serious about anyone.

19
00:01:00,545 --> 00:01:01,865
I know.

20
00:01:01,945 --> 00:01:03,745
But I’m not in a rush.

21
00:01:03,825 --> 00:01:09,185
You might think that now,
but in the future, who knows?

22
00:01:10,385 --> 00:01:12,145
You’re way too smart.

23
00:01:12,225 --> 00:01:14,745
You know, Ploy getting a stomachache today

24
00:01:14,825 --> 00:01:16,825
was obviously a setup to get us alone.

25
00:01:17,625 --> 00:01:21,385
If you really hated me,
you wouldn’t still be standing here.

26
00:01:25,345 --> 00:01:27,585
I’m only here because I pity you.

27
00:01:27,665 --> 00:01:29,105
You’re the chairwoman’s granddaughter.

28
00:01:29,185 --> 00:01:30,585
If nobody takes care of you,

29
00:01:30,665 --> 00:01:33,505
you'd be like a lost, pricey puppy.

30
00:01:35,425 --> 00:01:36,865
You really have a sharp tongue.

31
00:01:36,945 --> 00:01:39,305
Calling me a dog again.

32
00:01:40,505 --> 00:01:41,625
But it’s okay.

33
00:01:41,705 --> 00:01:43,425
At least I’m an expensive one.

34
00:01:45,705 --> 00:01:49,465
By the way, since you already
brought me food to taste,

35
00:01:51,145 --> 00:01:53,705
would you be interested
in adopting a dog too?

36
00:01:56,785 --> 00:01:57,625
That’s enough.

37
00:01:57,705 --> 00:01:59,665
Stop daydreaming already.

38
00:02:06,265 --> 00:02:07,705
There.

39
00:02:07,785 --> 00:02:09,985
After you finish, leave me a review too.

40
00:02:10,065 --> 00:02:12,145
You’ve already wasted
too much of my work time.

41
00:02:31,665 --> 00:02:32,585
Here.

42
00:02:50,585 --> 00:02:53,465
<i>The food is delicious,</i>
<i>but the chef looks even tastier.</i>

43
00:02:53,545 --> 00:02:57,065
<i>P.S. I’d still love to keep tasting more.</i>

44
00:02:57,145 --> 00:03:00,145
<i>If you're ready for another,</i>
<i>I'm just a call away.</i>

45
00:04:21,545 --> 00:04:23,345
<i>Your hot americano is ready.</i>

46
00:04:40,665 --> 00:04:41,585
I’m sorry.

47
00:04:41,665 --> 00:04:43,225
I didn’t mean to.

48
00:04:48,305 --> 00:04:49,225
Thank you.

49
00:04:49,305 --> 00:04:52,385
Once I'm done, I'll wash it
and return it to you right away.

50
00:05:04,265 --> 00:05:05,505
Mudmee.

51
00:05:07,465 --> 00:05:10,385
You startled me.

52
00:05:12,265 --> 00:05:14,425
Since when did you become so jumpy?

53
00:05:15,785 --> 00:05:18,345
Or are you thinking about someone?

54
00:05:20,425 --> 00:05:22,905
Shut up. Don’t be ridiculous.

55
00:05:24,425 --> 00:05:25,905
Who would I even think about?

56
00:05:27,945 --> 00:05:30,225
So, where did you go?

57
00:05:30,305 --> 00:05:32,665
Did you go bother Song again?

58
00:05:33,425 --> 00:05:36,905
Bother her? I was just flirting with her.

59
00:05:41,545 --> 00:05:42,545
Mudmee.

60
00:05:43,305 --> 00:05:45,785
Song has really put up a wall against me.

61
00:05:45,865 --> 00:05:47,585
It's so high that I’m losing confidence

62
00:05:47,665 --> 00:05:49,065
and wondering what’s wrong with me.

63
00:05:49,145 --> 00:05:51,825
I’m both pretty and rich.

64
00:05:51,905 --> 00:05:56,465
Okay, maybe my boobs are a little small,
but that’s most people’s type these days.

65
00:06:01,305 --> 00:06:02,905
You’re really confident, huh?

66
00:06:04,225 --> 00:06:05,745
Of course.

67
00:06:08,505 --> 00:06:13,505
So, do you think Song
is like ordinary people?

68
00:06:14,105 --> 00:06:16,305
No. She’s a rare item.

69
00:06:17,225 --> 00:06:18,265
Exactly.

70
00:06:19,065 --> 00:06:22,905
I think for Song,
if she’s going to like someone,

71
00:06:22,985 --> 00:06:24,745
there has to be more
of a reason than that.

72
00:06:24,825 --> 00:06:30,265
Not just being pretty, rich,
having small boobs, or big boobs.

73
00:06:30,905 --> 00:06:32,305
That alone isn’t enough.

74
00:06:34,225 --> 00:06:35,785
Then what kind of person does she like?

75
00:06:38,225 --> 00:06:39,065
No idea.

76
00:06:39,145 --> 00:06:41,345
I’ve only seen her work side.

77
00:06:41,425 --> 00:06:43,825
I know nothing about the rest.

78
00:06:44,785 --> 00:06:46,065
She’s hard to read.

79
00:06:56,025 --> 00:06:57,305
Mudmee.

80
00:06:57,385 --> 00:06:59,545
Then let’s turn it into work.

81
00:07:01,465 --> 00:07:02,305
Work?

82
00:07:17,945 --> 00:07:20,585
Bobis Magazine contacted me.

83
00:07:20,665 --> 00:07:23,065
They want to do
a special feature on our company.

84
00:07:23,665 --> 00:07:25,785
The concept is to inspire
the younger generation.

85
00:07:25,865 --> 00:07:30,545
And I'd love to pitch
a piece on researchers.

86
00:07:32,105 --> 00:07:34,265
So how do you want me to help?

87
00:07:34,345 --> 00:07:36,905
Well, by being that researcher.

88
00:07:37,545 --> 00:07:39,145
You want to interview me?

89
00:07:39,225 --> 00:07:41,945
Yes. Who could be more suitable than you?

90
00:07:42,025 --> 00:07:44,265
You’re our company’s
outstanding researcher.

91
00:07:45,825 --> 00:07:48,865
I think I’ll pass.

92
00:07:55,345 --> 00:07:56,825
Song.

93
00:07:56,905 --> 00:08:01,385
I truly believe your story
can inspire readers.

94
00:08:01,905 --> 00:08:05,185
And I also want to use this chance
to promote our company at the same time.

95
00:08:06,705 --> 00:08:08,065
I want people to know

96
00:08:08,145 --> 00:08:11,785
that food researchers are one
of the organization’s driving forces.

97
00:08:13,345 --> 00:08:16,665
If our company has good researchers,

98
00:08:16,745 --> 00:08:19,865
we can guarantee the products
we release will be high quality.

99
00:08:20,785 --> 00:08:22,145
Please help me out.

100
00:08:27,945 --> 00:08:31,785
If it’ll benefit the company,
then I’m happy to do it.

101
00:08:33,024 --> 00:08:33,945
Thank you.

102
00:08:35,425 --> 00:08:37,465
And there’s one more thing.

103
00:08:37,545 --> 00:08:40,985
I know Piang’s been trying
to flirt with you lately.

104
00:08:41,065 --> 00:08:42,664
It’s kind of funny.

105
00:08:42,745 --> 00:08:46,225
In all my life, I’ve never seen
my little sister try this hard before.

106
00:08:46,305 --> 00:08:48,225
She must really like you.

107
00:08:49,065 --> 00:08:52,385
But I also know you’re not playing along.

108
00:08:52,465 --> 00:08:53,705
And that she annoys you.

109
00:08:53,785 --> 00:08:56,065
If it gets too much, you can scold her.

110
00:08:56,145 --> 00:08:59,265
I already did, but she just won’t listen.

111
00:08:59,985 --> 00:09:01,745
Honestly, she does annoy me.

112
00:09:06,585 --> 00:09:08,665
But not that much, Boss.

113
00:09:08,745 --> 00:09:10,905
I think I can handle it.

114
00:09:23,185 --> 00:09:24,745
Who do you want me to interview?

115
00:09:28,745 --> 00:09:30,425
This person right here.

116
00:09:31,305 --> 00:09:33,705
I want to know her life story.

117
00:09:33,785 --> 00:09:36,425
But I want to do it in a more subtle way.

118
00:09:36,505 --> 00:09:38,425
But don’t worry
about your interview flopping.

119
00:09:38,505 --> 00:09:41,025
She’s our company’s leading researcher.

120
00:09:41,105 --> 00:09:43,465
She’s talented and hot.

121
00:09:45,025 --> 00:09:46,185
Wait, this is Song.

122
00:09:47,425 --> 00:09:48,585
You know her?

123
00:09:49,865 --> 00:09:51,905
She’s a freelance model.

124
00:09:51,985 --> 00:09:54,505
I met her a few times
during my internship.

125
00:09:55,105 --> 00:09:56,705
She's a researcher at your company?

126
00:09:56,785 --> 00:09:58,905
You knew her and didn’t tell me?

127
00:09:58,985 --> 00:10:00,745
How the hell was I supposed to know, girl?

128
00:10:00,825 --> 00:10:04,785
Remember the girl I met on the dating app
who used a cat photo as her profile?

129
00:10:06,265 --> 00:10:07,545
That was her.

130
00:10:09,305 --> 00:10:10,185
What a coincidence.

131
00:10:10,265 --> 00:10:11,905
Coincidence my ass.

132
00:10:12,425 --> 00:10:14,185
It’s fate.

133
00:10:15,545 --> 00:10:18,945
Why say you're okay giving
your virginity to a stranger,

134
00:10:19,025 --> 00:10:20,865
when you ended up falling for her?

135
00:10:21,465 --> 00:10:22,785
You’re so weak.

136
00:10:22,865 --> 00:10:25,345
Yeah, yeah. Say whatever you want.

137
00:10:25,425 --> 00:10:31,305
But Song is someone I want to date,
marry, and build a family with.

138
00:10:31,385 --> 00:10:33,705
Even Mudmee volunteered to help me.

139
00:10:33,785 --> 00:10:37,785
So as my best friend,
you have no right to refuse.

140
00:10:40,065 --> 00:10:42,425
I already sent you the script
I want you to ask her.

141
00:10:44,305 --> 00:10:46,785
These are all personal questions.

142
00:10:46,865 --> 00:10:48,385
Of course. I want to know.

143
00:10:48,465 --> 00:10:51,265
As for the work-related questions,
you can handle those yourself.

144
00:10:51,345 --> 00:10:53,345
That’s your job, right, bestie?

145
00:10:53,425 --> 00:10:54,265
Seriously?

146
00:11:05,425 --> 00:11:08,665
<i>All my life, I’ve never seen</i>
<i>my little sister try this hard before.</i>

147
00:11:08,745 --> 00:11:10,825
She must really like you.

148
00:11:43,625 --> 00:11:45,625
THE FOOD IS DELICIOUS
BUT THE CHEF LOOKS EVEN TASTIER

149
00:12:32,665 --> 00:12:35,465
You actually dressed
the way I asked you to.

150
00:12:36,665 --> 00:12:39,425
So, do you like it?

151
00:12:40,465 --> 00:12:41,825
I like it a lot.

152
00:13:38,905 --> 00:13:40,385
You’re really clumsy.

153
00:13:42,945 --> 00:13:45,265
And who told you
to dress like this at the office?

154
00:13:45,345 --> 00:13:47,225
Do you want everyone staring at you?

155
00:13:48,985 --> 00:13:50,105
Yes.

156
00:13:50,665 --> 00:13:51,905
But not everyone.

157
00:13:53,585 --> 00:13:55,505
I only want you to look at me.

158
00:13:59,465 --> 00:14:01,305
I happened to see that this afternoon,

159
00:14:01,385 --> 00:14:03,265
you’re doing an interview for a magazine.

160
00:14:03,945 --> 00:14:08,905
So, I wanted to dress up nicely
in the style you like.

161
00:14:09,545 --> 00:14:12,345
Why? They’re not interviewing you.

162
00:14:14,025 --> 00:14:19,945
Just think of it as me dressing up
to cheer you on instead.

163
00:14:25,225 --> 00:14:26,625
<i>-What should we eat?</i>
<i>-Pizza?</i>

164
00:14:26,705 --> 00:14:29,265
<i>Sure. Then for lunch, we can go eat…</i>

165
00:14:29,985 --> 00:14:30,865
together.

166
00:14:32,785 --> 00:14:33,785
Piang.

167
00:14:35,745 --> 00:14:36,825
What happened?

168
00:14:38,065 --> 00:14:39,825
Nothing.

169
00:14:39,905 --> 00:14:42,465
I was just being clumsy and almost fell.

170
00:14:42,545 --> 00:14:45,385
But Song caught me in time.

171
00:14:47,025 --> 00:14:49,905
-That’s wonderful.
-That’s wonderful.

172
00:14:51,225 --> 00:14:53,185
We were about to go eat, Piang.

173
00:14:53,265 --> 00:14:54,225
Would you come with us?

174
00:14:54,305 --> 00:14:55,945
Yeah. We’re heading to the elevator
in the other building.

175
00:14:56,025 --> 00:14:58,185
-Come with us, Piang.
-Can I really?

176
00:14:58,265 --> 00:14:59,545
-Of course.
-Of course.

177
00:14:59,625 --> 00:15:01,345
You’re the company owner.

178
00:15:01,425 --> 00:15:03,785
Nobody would dare complain about you.

179
00:15:05,585 --> 00:15:06,865
-Let’s go.
-Let’s go together.

180
00:15:07,705 --> 00:15:08,545
Let’s go.

181
00:15:09,865 --> 00:15:11,105
Wait.

182
00:15:12,265 --> 00:15:13,465
Where did she go?

183
00:15:14,785 --> 00:15:15,505
Here.

184
00:15:23,545 --> 00:15:27,145
You know, I think Song
is finally starting to waver. Or maybe…

185
00:15:27,225 --> 00:15:30,705
the Arctic wolf is about to fall
for a Holland Lop bunny.

186
00:15:31,505 --> 00:15:32,545
Definitely.

187
00:15:32,625 --> 00:15:35,745
Then hyenas like us
have to support this, right?

188
00:15:35,825 --> 00:15:37,465
Idiot. Gross. What hyenas?

189
00:15:37,545 --> 00:15:38,905
Think of another animal.

190
00:15:38,985 --> 00:15:40,425
Then what about monitor lizards?

191
00:15:40,505 --> 00:15:42,185
What monitor lizards? They're in the park.

192
00:15:42,265 --> 00:15:44,625
-Wait for me.
-Everyone, wait for me.

193
00:15:44,705 --> 00:15:45,665
Wait for me.

194
00:15:45,745 --> 00:15:47,945
-The elevator’s crowded. Wait for me.
-Come on.

195
00:15:48,025 --> 00:15:51,105
What are you eating today? I want noodles.

196
00:15:52,345 --> 00:15:53,505
Then eat noodles.

197
00:15:53,585 --> 00:15:55,665
And what are you eating? Same place?

198
00:15:55,745 --> 00:15:58,505
I’ve never come to the company before,
so I don’t know what’s good here.

199
00:15:59,505 --> 00:16:00,745
You’ll know once we're there.

200
00:16:01,625 --> 00:16:04,185
-But I wanted to know…
-Elevator's here.

201
00:16:04,265 --> 00:16:05,865
-Hurry up. Go.
-Go.

202
00:16:05,945 --> 00:16:08,345
-Let's get in.
-I’m coming too, wait.

203
00:16:08,425 --> 00:16:10,065
Go. Press it already.

204
00:16:22,665 --> 00:16:24,065
It’s me, Piang.

205
00:16:24,145 --> 00:16:26,145
The chairwoman’s granddaughter.

206
00:16:26,225 --> 00:16:27,905
It’s me.

207
00:16:29,625 --> 00:16:31,665
Yes, ma’am. I know who you are.

208
00:16:31,745 --> 00:16:36,265
It’s just that employees like us
have limited break time, Miss Piang.

209
00:16:36,345 --> 00:16:39,545
Besides, our break is almost over too.

210
00:16:39,625 --> 00:16:41,425
-Right?
-Yeah, yeah.

211
00:16:41,505 --> 00:16:43,585
-That's right.
-Yeah.

212
00:16:44,785 --> 00:16:48,465
So if possible, could you let us go first?

213
00:16:52,225 --> 00:16:55,105
-Fine.
-Okay.

214
00:16:56,585 --> 00:16:58,305
Thank you. So kind of you.

215
00:17:00,145 --> 00:17:01,185
-Song, go.
-Song, go ahead.

216
00:17:01,265 --> 00:17:03,785
-Go get her.
-Finally, we get to go.

217
00:17:21,825 --> 00:17:22,665
You guys go ahead.

218
00:17:23,625 --> 00:17:25,585
Hurry.

219
00:17:25,665 --> 00:17:27,545
-Hurry, hurry.
-Bye.

220
00:17:37,385 --> 00:17:39,825
Wait for me.

221
00:17:39,905 --> 00:17:41,425
You didn’t want to leave me alone,

222
00:17:41,505 --> 00:17:43,065
that’s why you got out, right?

223
00:17:43,145 --> 00:17:45,305
Why are you walking away from me now?

224
00:17:45,385 --> 00:17:47,345
Who told you? I only did it

225
00:17:47,425 --> 00:17:49,105
beacuse it was too crowded,

226
00:17:49,185 --> 00:17:50,305
so I walked out.

227
00:17:51,465 --> 00:17:53,145
Then what about this jacket?

228
00:17:53,225 --> 00:17:57,345
If you didn’t care about me,
you wouldn’t have let me wear it, right?

229
00:17:57,425 --> 00:18:00,225
You dressed so revealingly.

230
00:18:00,305 --> 00:18:03,945
Whether it was Namprow or Ploy,
I’d do the same for anyone.

231
00:18:05,065 --> 00:18:06,105
Not true.

232
00:18:06,185 --> 00:18:07,865
You’re falling for me.

233
00:18:07,945 --> 00:18:11,025
You dummy, stop imagining things.

234
00:18:11,105 --> 00:18:13,825
And stop meddling in my life already.

235
00:18:13,905 --> 00:18:16,065
I don’t feel anything for you.

236
00:18:16,145 --> 00:18:17,865
And I never will.

237
00:18:18,585 --> 00:18:20,065
I don’t believe you.

238
00:18:20,145 --> 00:18:21,545
You do feel something.

239
00:18:21,625 --> 00:18:22,905
You just won’t admit it.

240
00:18:22,985 --> 00:18:24,505
Listen.

241
00:18:24,585 --> 00:18:26,505
I’m not a complicated person.

242
00:18:26,585 --> 00:18:30,145
If I really had feelings for someone,
I wouldn’t run away.

243
00:18:30,865 --> 00:18:32,945
I’d even look for chances
to get closer to them.

244
00:18:33,545 --> 00:18:36,705
But you, you’ve never crossed my mind.

245
00:18:37,425 --> 00:18:40,465
Even that night, I don’t remember a thing.

246
00:18:43,905 --> 00:18:47,785
Then let me help refresh your memory.

247
00:18:48,345 --> 00:18:49,345
How about that?

248
00:19:23,465 --> 00:19:24,465
Stop.

249
00:19:27,985 --> 00:19:32,265
That jacket, I spent almost
my entire month’s salary on it.

250
00:19:33,705 --> 00:19:36,105
Pick it up right now. It’ll get dirty.

251
00:19:37,505 --> 00:19:38,545
Song!

252
00:19:39,345 --> 00:19:40,465
Pick it up.

253
00:19:48,025 --> 00:19:49,425
And put it back on properly.

254
00:19:55,985 --> 00:20:00,145
Don’t take it off again
until you get home, understand?

255
00:20:17,745 --> 00:20:20,105
<i>I’m here already. Where are you?</i>

256
00:20:20,185 --> 00:20:21,585
Yeah, I’m coming right now.

257
00:20:29,225 --> 00:20:31,625
These are the questions
for your interview.

258
00:20:31,705 --> 00:20:33,745
Most of them are work-related questions.

259
00:20:34,345 --> 00:20:36,105
There are a few personal ones too.

260
00:20:36,185 --> 00:20:38,625
So if there’s anything
you’re not comfortable answering,

261
00:20:38,705 --> 00:20:40,225
just let me know.

262
00:20:40,305 --> 00:20:42,545
We’re recording this, not live streaming.

263
00:20:42,625 --> 00:20:44,585
We can pause anytime.

264
00:20:44,665 --> 00:20:45,625
Okay.

265
00:20:47,105 --> 00:20:49,065
Do you have any questions, Song?

266
00:20:50,705 --> 00:20:51,985
Just one.

267
00:20:53,625 --> 00:20:55,905
You’re the CEO of Bobis.

268
00:20:56,425 --> 00:20:58,985
Why are you interviewing me yourself?

269
00:21:02,585 --> 00:21:05,265
I was assigned to do it.

270
00:21:11,265 --> 00:21:13,305
-Song, are you ready?
-Ready.

271
00:21:13,385 --> 00:21:14,705
Okay.

272
00:21:16,625 --> 00:21:17,505
Hi.

273
00:21:17,585 --> 00:21:18,985
Hello.

274
00:21:21,905 --> 00:21:23,265
Camera ready?

275
00:21:23,345 --> 00:21:24,785
Ready.

276
00:21:24,865 --> 00:21:25,865
Camera.

277
00:21:25,945 --> 00:21:27,025
Recording.

278
00:21:27,105 --> 00:21:28,625
Action.

279
00:21:29,145 --> 00:21:31,665
My name is Song Sadanun Warakij.

280
00:21:31,745 --> 00:21:34,225
I’m a food researcher at One Two Six Food.

281
00:21:34,305 --> 00:21:36,105
The recipient of the Mega Excellent Award

282
00:21:36,185 --> 00:21:38,745
for Outstanding Researcher
three years in a row.

283
00:21:38,825 --> 00:21:41,985
Could you tell us a little more
about this award?

284
00:21:43,025 --> 00:21:46,985
Sure. The Mega Excellent Award
for Outstanding Researcher

285
00:21:47,065 --> 00:21:50,585
is based on accumulated scores
from each research team

286
00:21:50,665 --> 00:21:52,985
working on various company projects.

287
00:21:53,705 --> 00:21:59,185
Whether it’s OEM projects from clients
or projects we develop ourselves,

288
00:21:59,265 --> 00:22:03,745
the team with the highest score
wins the award for their team leader.

289
00:22:03,825 --> 00:22:06,105
So you’re the team leader?

290
00:22:06,185 --> 00:22:07,265
Yes.

291
00:22:08,865 --> 00:22:12,105
Then you must be really good at cooking.

292
00:22:12,185 --> 00:22:13,865
I can cook a little.

293
00:22:13,945 --> 00:22:16,945
But honestly, the one who’s much
better than me is my grandma.

294
00:22:19,065 --> 00:22:22,865
My grandma is the reason
I became interested in food.

295
00:22:23,505 --> 00:22:27,105
That’s why I decided to study
Food Science and Culinary Arts.

296
00:22:28,665 --> 00:22:30,185
So I wouldn't step on her toes.

297
00:22:31,065 --> 00:22:33,825
So you must be very close to your grandma.

298
00:22:34,625 --> 00:22:37,625
Could you tell us a little about her?

299
00:22:41,705 --> 00:22:43,985
My grandma is very kind.

300
00:22:44,065 --> 00:22:45,305
She’s modern-minded.

301
00:22:45,905 --> 00:22:48,865
She raised me more like a friend
than a guardian.

302
00:22:50,065 --> 00:22:52,185
What about your parents?

303
00:23:09,065 --> 00:23:12,225
Several years ago, something happened.

304
00:23:12,745 --> 00:23:15,105
My mother suddenly became ill.

305
00:23:15,625 --> 00:23:19,585
So my father took her abroad.

306
00:23:23,305 --> 00:23:28,825
Would you tell us
what exactly happened back then?

307
00:23:35,305 --> 00:23:39,705
<i>Song, I’m sorry.</i>
<i>I really can’t stay anymore.</i>

308
00:23:39,785 --> 00:23:41,665
Neung!

309
00:23:59,825 --> 00:24:01,225
Pause the interview.

310
00:24:01,825 --> 00:24:02,785
Cut.

311
00:24:03,385 --> 00:24:05,225
Are you okay, Song?

312
00:24:05,945 --> 00:24:06,905
Are you okay?

313
00:24:06,985 --> 00:24:08,785
Can someone get her some water?

314
00:24:10,625 --> 00:24:11,745
Here's water.

315
00:24:37,545 --> 00:24:38,865
I’m okay.

316
00:24:40,065 --> 00:24:41,825
Are you alright?

317
00:24:44,505 --> 00:24:45,865
I’m fine.

318
00:24:46,545 --> 00:24:50,345
But can we skip
the family-related questions?

319
00:24:51,025 --> 00:24:53,345
That's all I'm willing to share.

320
00:24:53,425 --> 00:24:54,265
Of course.

321
00:24:54,345 --> 00:24:57,105
In that case, let’s move on
to another part of the interview.

322
00:24:57,865 --> 00:24:58,865
Okay.

323
00:24:59,385 --> 00:25:00,785
Let’s continue filming.

324
00:25:04,265 --> 00:25:06,065
Song, are you ready?

325
00:25:07,785 --> 00:25:08,825
Ready.

326
00:25:12,385 --> 00:25:13,705
Is the camera ready?

327
00:25:14,225 --> 00:25:16,985
<i>There’s a package delivery for Mudmee.</i>

328
00:25:20,745 --> 00:25:21,785
I’ll be right back.

329
00:25:24,585 --> 00:25:27,625
SENDER: KWANRIN PINIJPHAN

330
00:25:39,145 --> 00:25:40,385
Kwanrin.

331
00:25:42,305 --> 00:25:43,825
One Two Four.

332
00:25:58,065 --> 00:25:59,385
<i>Hello, Mudmee.</i>

333
00:25:59,465 --> 00:26:01,785
-Hello.
<i>-It’s been a while since we talked.</i>

334
00:26:01,865 --> 00:26:02,905
A little while.

335
00:26:02,985 --> 00:26:05,985
The chair I ordered
from One Two Four has been perfect.

336
00:26:06,065 --> 00:26:08,785
Everyone says
it’s beautiful and well-designed.

337
00:26:08,865 --> 00:26:10,265
<i>Thank you so much.</i>

338
00:26:10,345 --> 00:26:13,025
<i>So, is there anything I can help you with?</i>

339
00:26:13,705 --> 00:26:18,185
Well, the other day, I went to a café
and happened to meet a woman

340
00:26:18,265 --> 00:26:19,825
named Kwanrin.

341
00:26:20,425 --> 00:26:24,265
I saw her holding documents
from One Two Four.

342
00:26:24,345 --> 00:26:26,825
Has she started working there?

343
00:26:26,905 --> 00:26:28,705
<i>Oh, Kwanrin.</i>

344
00:26:28,785 --> 00:26:32,065
<i>Yes. We just hired her</i>
<i>as a Project Manager.</i>

345
00:26:32,145 --> 00:26:34,105
<i>She only started working here</i>
<i>a few days ago.</i>

346
00:26:34,185 --> 00:26:35,945
<i>So you know her too?</i>

347
00:26:36,025 --> 00:26:37,305
<i>Oh right.</i>

348
00:26:37,385 --> 00:26:39,745
<i>She lives in the same house</i>
<i>as the chairwoman too.</i>

349
00:26:39,825 --> 00:26:41,825
<i>She’s close</i>
<i>to the chairman’s daughter-in-law.</i>

350
00:26:41,905 --> 00:26:44,065
<i>She even helps take care</i>
<i>of the chairwoman’s fish.</i>

351
00:26:44,145 --> 00:26:47,465
<i>Honestly, she could’ve gotten in</i>
<i>through connections if she wanted.</i>

352
00:26:47,545 --> 00:26:49,145
<i>But Kwanrin…</i>

353
00:26:50,865 --> 00:26:53,945
We’ve gathered almost
all the information we need now.

354
00:26:54,745 --> 00:27:00,345
So I have a few more questions
I’d like to ask you,

355
00:27:00,425 --> 00:27:02,105
on behalf of viewers across the country

356
00:27:02,185 --> 00:27:06,105
including all of your fans
who came to support you today.

357
00:27:06,185 --> 00:27:08,745
You dedicate yourself to work so much,

358
00:27:09,465 --> 00:27:11,505
how do you make time for your partner?

359
00:27:19,665 --> 00:27:21,785
I don’t need to make time
because I don’t have one.

360
00:27:26,225 --> 00:27:28,705
I choose to focus only on work.

361
00:27:31,905 --> 00:27:35,945
I believe work won’t betray us
the way love does.

362
00:27:36,025 --> 00:27:40,025
Then hypothetically,
if you were to fall in love,

363
00:27:40,105 --> 00:27:44,705
what kind of person would be your type?

364
00:27:44,785 --> 00:27:46,625
The one you want to spend your life with.

365
00:27:56,785 --> 00:27:57,785
Someone mature.

366
00:27:58,785 --> 00:28:02,465
Not about age, but their mindset
and behavior must be proper.

367
00:28:02,545 --> 00:28:04,265
From the way they dress
to their personality.

368
00:28:04,345 --> 00:28:05,585
One who understands things right away,

369
00:28:05,665 --> 00:28:07,985
not clingy, not childish,
not chasing after me.

370
00:28:08,065 --> 00:28:10,785
And most importantly,
they must have something of their own.

371
00:28:10,865 --> 00:28:13,985
Not relying on their family’s success
for the rest of their life.

372
00:28:21,705 --> 00:28:23,025
Excuse me.

373
00:28:23,105 --> 00:28:24,665
<i>Did you hear that clearly, bestie?</i>

374
00:28:24,745 --> 00:28:27,505
<i>The type she likes</i>
<i>is the complete opposite of you.</i>

375
00:28:27,585 --> 00:28:29,065
<i>I’m laughing my ass off.</i>

376
00:28:29,145 --> 00:28:30,585
<i>Do you really think</i>
<i>someone like Piangrawin</i>

377
00:28:30,665 --> 00:28:32,305
<i>would be shaken by that?</i>

378
00:28:32,385 --> 00:28:33,425
<i>Dream on.</i>

379
00:28:35,225 --> 00:28:36,225
That’s everything, right?

380
00:28:36,305 --> 00:28:37,465
Yes, all done.

381
00:28:38,745 --> 00:28:40,105
That’s a wrap.

382
00:28:40,185 --> 00:28:41,865
Thank you so much.

383
00:28:43,065 --> 00:28:45,385
-Thank you so much, Song.
-You’re welcome.

384
00:28:45,465 --> 00:28:47,705
-Today went smoothly.
-Piang, how did it go?

385
00:28:47,785 --> 00:28:49,785
Please make yourself comfortable, Song.

386
00:28:49,865 --> 00:28:51,025
Please take care of her.

387
00:28:51,105 --> 00:28:52,225
Okay.

388
00:29:01,265 --> 00:29:03,705
Mon. Did something happen?

389
00:29:04,225 --> 00:29:05,945
Nothing really, Mud.

390
00:29:06,025 --> 00:29:08,465
We just need to give Piang
some time to process things.

391
00:29:10,505 --> 00:29:11,585
Process things?

392
00:29:45,345 --> 00:29:46,865
Come on, Song.

393
00:29:46,945 --> 00:29:49,865
Modeling has always been my dream.

394
00:29:50,585 --> 00:29:52,585
Will you go audition with me?

395
00:29:53,825 --> 00:29:55,265
Please?

396
00:29:58,225 --> 00:30:01,105
At least, if I don’t pass the audition

397
00:30:01,185 --> 00:30:04,905
but you do, I won’t feel so bad about it.

398
00:30:04,985 --> 00:30:07,865
If you don’t pass, how would I?

399
00:30:07,945 --> 00:30:09,065
We look alike.

400
00:30:10,865 --> 00:30:13,145
We only look alike on the outside.

401
00:30:13,225 --> 00:30:15,705
But in every other way,
we’re completely different.

402
00:30:16,305 --> 00:30:18,465
You have this presence.

403
00:30:18,545 --> 00:30:22,425
Some kind of energy
from within that I don’t have.

404
00:30:22,505 --> 00:30:23,385
So dramatic.

405
00:30:24,185 --> 00:30:25,505
I’m serious.

406
00:30:26,265 --> 00:30:28,345
That’s really how I feel.

407
00:30:29,025 --> 00:30:31,945
You’re way stronger than I am.

408
00:30:36,465 --> 00:30:37,865
No thanks.

409
00:30:37,945 --> 00:30:40,025
I don’t like being in front of cameras.

410
00:30:40,105 --> 00:30:43,145
I prefer being in front
of stoves and test tubes.

411
00:30:44,985 --> 00:30:47,465
Fine, I won’t force you.

412
00:30:50,425 --> 00:30:52,665
But can you promise me one thing?

413
00:30:54,025 --> 00:30:58,745
If one day I’m gone
and I still haven’t achieved my dream,

414
00:30:58,825 --> 00:31:00,545
can you do it for me?

415
00:31:00,625 --> 00:31:02,145
Why would you say that?

416
00:31:02,865 --> 00:31:04,385
Just promise me already.

417
00:31:06,305 --> 00:31:07,945
Come on.

418
00:31:09,745 --> 00:31:11,585
Please, Song.

419
00:31:15,185 --> 00:31:16,705
Fine, I promise.

420
00:32:11,385 --> 00:32:12,745
This outfit won’t work.

421
00:32:28,545 --> 00:32:29,945
Is the skirt too short?

422
00:32:51,905 --> 00:32:52,945
So tacky.

423
00:32:53,025 --> 00:32:55,905
But whatever, this is the style she likes.

424
00:33:02,185 --> 00:33:03,345
Nope.

425
00:33:09,985 --> 00:33:11,945
Hello, Song.

426
00:33:13,745 --> 00:33:15,025
No, not this either.

427
00:33:38,345 --> 00:33:39,945
This looks proper.

428
00:33:49,385 --> 00:33:50,705
INCOMING CALL

429
00:34:02,545 --> 00:34:04,265
Hello, Ploy.

430
00:34:04,345 --> 00:34:05,625
<i>Hello, Piang.</i>

431
00:34:05,705 --> 00:34:09,264
Someone told me what Song
said in the interview today.

432
00:34:09,985 --> 00:34:11,945
Don’t overthink it.

433
00:34:12,025 --> 00:34:15,065
I think she was just messing with you.

434
00:34:15,145 --> 00:34:18,225
I think so too,
but I still want to change for her.

435
00:34:18,304 --> 00:34:21,065
Actually, it’s good you called.

436
00:34:21,145 --> 00:34:24,105
I think I already have everything
she’s looking for

437
00:34:24,185 --> 00:34:28,105
except one thing.
I need to find something of my own to do.

438
00:34:28,185 --> 00:34:31,105
But I honestly don’t know

439
00:34:31,185 --> 00:34:32,545
where to even start.

440
00:34:34,985 --> 00:34:38,385
Is there anything
you’re especially interested in?

441
00:34:39,824 --> 00:34:41,225
I'm interested in Song, duh.

442
00:34:42,145 --> 00:34:45,425
That, I know. But I mean,

443
00:34:45,505 --> 00:34:46,905
is there anything you like doing

444
00:34:46,985 --> 00:34:48,985
<i>or especially enjoy eating?</i>

445
00:34:49,065 --> 00:34:52,465
<i>Maybe you could use that as inspiration.</i>

446
00:34:52,545 --> 00:34:54,665
I don’t really have anything
I especially like.

447
00:34:59,345 --> 00:35:01,785
Or try Song's interests?

448
00:35:02,545 --> 00:35:04,745
Her interests?

449
00:35:18,505 --> 00:35:19,865
Mudmee.

450
00:35:19,945 --> 00:35:21,785
You still don’t knock
before entering, Piang.

451
00:35:22,465 --> 00:35:24,505
I want to open a matcha café.

452
00:35:27,585 --> 00:35:28,905
I’m not sick.

453
00:35:30,225 --> 00:35:31,145
You are sick.

454
00:35:31,225 --> 00:35:32,705
I’m not sick.

455
00:35:34,385 --> 00:35:37,425
So, what made you want to do that?

456
00:35:39,465 --> 00:35:42,385
Don’t tell me this is about Song again.

457
00:35:46,225 --> 00:35:47,465
You know me too well.

458
00:35:47,545 --> 00:35:50,265
Yes. I want to have something of my own.

459
00:35:50,345 --> 00:35:52,665
I want to become
the kind of person she likes.

460
00:35:52,745 --> 00:35:55,625
Please, help me.

461
00:36:08,425 --> 00:36:09,785
Fine.

462
00:36:09,865 --> 00:36:13,825
I’ll handle the location
and the shop decoration too.

463
00:36:14,905 --> 00:36:17,905
Mudmee, you’re the sweetest.

464
00:36:17,985 --> 00:36:19,425
I love you the most.

465
00:36:28,625 --> 00:36:31,225
Piang wants to open a matcha café.

466
00:36:32,545 --> 00:36:34,145
A matcha café?

467
00:36:34,225 --> 00:36:36,105
Yeah. She said she wants to do it.

468
00:36:36,185 --> 00:36:38,785
She said she wants to
have something of her own.

469
00:36:40,145 --> 00:36:43,345
Honestly, I do want to support her idea.

470
00:36:43,425 --> 00:36:46,065
I want her to try working
on something for once.

471
00:36:46,145 --> 00:36:48,465
But I don’t know anything
about this kind of business,

472
00:36:48,545 --> 00:36:49,905
so I came to ask for your advice.

473
00:36:49,985 --> 00:36:53,545
I heard you’ve worked
on matcha-related products before.

474
00:36:54,065 --> 00:36:55,705
Maybe you could give us some advice.

475
00:36:57,465 --> 00:37:01,185
Boss, you really came to the right person.

476
00:37:01,265 --> 00:37:03,825
Not only did Song develop
this product before,

477
00:37:03,905 --> 00:37:06,065
she’s also a huge matcha lover.

478
00:37:06,145 --> 00:37:09,145
She loves it so much
she makes me buy it for her every morning.

479
00:37:27,265 --> 00:37:30,025
Then I guess I’ll have to trouble you…

480
00:37:34,545 --> 00:37:36,105
I mean, Miss Song.

481
00:38:35,865 --> 00:38:38,305
I thought you said
you didn’t like people chasing after you.

482
00:38:38,825 --> 00:38:40,385
Then why are you doing it yourself?

483
00:38:41,025 --> 00:38:45,065
That matcha café thing, don’t you realize
you’re doing way too much?

484
00:38:47,425 --> 00:38:48,865
What do you mean?

485
00:38:48,945 --> 00:38:49,985
I’m not playing around.

486
00:38:50,065 --> 00:38:51,425
I’m serious.

487
00:38:51,505 --> 00:38:52,905
I really want something of my own.

488
00:38:54,065 --> 00:38:55,465
You think I’d believe you?

489
00:38:56,385 --> 00:38:58,145
Believe it or not, that’s up to you.

490
00:38:59,305 --> 00:39:02,425
I mean, Miss Song, we’re adults already.

491
00:39:02,505 --> 00:39:04,465
Shouldn’t one explanation be enough?

492
00:39:05,865 --> 00:39:07,345
Miss Piang.

493
00:39:09,945 --> 00:39:11,905
I still need to discuss the café.

494
00:39:12,505 --> 00:39:13,385
Stop following me.

495
00:39:13,465 --> 00:39:15,905
Stop pestering me,
and stop clinging to me too.

496
00:39:17,345 --> 00:39:18,185
Understood?

497
00:39:21,625 --> 00:39:23,345
That crazy kid.

498
00:39:56,505 --> 00:39:58,945
Excuse me, are you Matika?

499
00:40:22,505 --> 00:40:23,865
Yes.

500
00:40:23,945 --> 00:40:27,545
You’re Kwanrin from One Two Four, right?

501
00:40:30,265 --> 00:40:31,625
What a coincidence.

502
00:40:35,865 --> 00:40:38,025
I should apologize,

503
00:40:38,105 --> 00:40:40,505
for requesting your company
to send you over so urgently.

504
00:40:40,585 --> 00:40:43,545
This project is a bit rushed.

505
00:40:44,825 --> 00:40:47,625
It’s totally fine. It’s my job anyway.

506
00:40:47,705 --> 00:40:50,305
So what do we need to do today?

507
00:40:50,385 --> 00:40:53,385
We need to measure the space,

508
00:40:53,465 --> 00:40:56,585
take your brief and pass it
to the interior designer.

509
00:40:56,665 --> 00:41:01,145
After that, I’ll help oversee everything
until the project is completed.

510
00:41:03,225 --> 00:41:04,465
That’s great.

511
00:41:04,545 --> 00:41:05,945
We’ll get to see each other again.

512
00:41:09,225 --> 00:41:11,465
Then let’s get started.

513
00:41:12,585 --> 00:41:13,945
Come here, I’ll help.

514
00:41:14,945 --> 00:41:16,265
You don’t have to.

515
00:41:16,345 --> 00:41:17,945
You’re the CEO.

516
00:41:18,025 --> 00:41:20,345
I doubt you’re used to this kind of work.

517
00:41:22,545 --> 00:41:23,505
Try me.

518
00:41:44,545 --> 00:41:45,945
This side is 2.5 meters wide.

519
00:41:46,705 --> 00:41:50,305
If we place the counter here,
the morning light should hit just right.

520
00:41:50,385 --> 00:41:52,745
Perfect for customers
who want to make content.

521
00:41:52,825 --> 00:41:55,385
But in the afternoon,
the sunlight will probably be too strong.

522
00:41:55,465 --> 00:41:59,865
We should install
heat-blocking film or sun blinds.

523
00:41:59,945 --> 00:42:02,865
That way the coffee machines
won’t be exposed to direct heat.

524
00:42:02,945 --> 00:42:05,025
As for the materials, I'm not fussy.

525
00:42:05,105 --> 00:42:08,665
As long as it keeps a Zen tone
to match the name Zen Su Garden.

526
00:42:13,105 --> 00:42:14,185
See?

527
00:42:14,265 --> 00:42:17,585
Some CEOs can do more than you think.

528
00:43:31,745 --> 00:43:32,745
You.

529
00:43:34,585 --> 00:43:35,585
You.

530
00:43:37,785 --> 00:43:38,945
Piang.

531
00:43:40,065 --> 00:43:41,265
Piang.

532
00:43:57,345 --> 00:43:58,865
Did you finish already?

533
00:44:00,985 --> 00:44:02,745
Only the classic menu items.

534
00:44:02,825 --> 00:44:04,545
The signature menu is still left.

535
00:44:04,625 --> 00:44:05,825
It needs a story.

536
00:44:06,745 --> 00:44:08,625
Since you’re the shop owner,

537
00:44:08,705 --> 00:44:11,945
I need to ask you first
before I can come up with it.

538
00:44:13,825 --> 00:44:14,825
Sure.

539
00:44:14,905 --> 00:44:17,185
You can ask me anything you want to know.

540
00:44:24,425 --> 00:44:27,785
Do you have any childhood memories
that are especially meaningful to you?

541
00:44:36,145 --> 00:44:37,225
Not really.

542
00:44:38,745 --> 00:44:40,625
My life was never very exciting.

543
00:44:40,705 --> 00:44:44,385
It felt like everything
had already been decided by my grandma.

544
00:44:44,465 --> 00:44:45,905
I just followed along.

545
00:44:46,825 --> 00:44:47,945
Really?

546
00:44:48,545 --> 00:44:50,505
You seem so strong-willed.

547
00:44:51,025 --> 00:44:52,985
You don’t look like someone
who listens to others,

548
00:44:53,825 --> 00:44:55,265
even if it’s your grandma.

549
00:44:56,065 --> 00:44:57,545
Not about everything.

550
00:44:57,625 --> 00:45:00,105
But if it’s something
I can accept, I will.

551
00:45:00,185 --> 00:45:03,785
After all, Grandma only
has me and Mudmee left.

552
00:45:05,185 --> 00:45:10,225
My parents both died
in an accident when I was little.

553
00:45:16,985 --> 00:45:19,145
Your parents died,
and you can still smile?

554
00:45:21,945 --> 00:45:23,985
It’s been a long time already.

555
00:45:24,905 --> 00:45:31,865
Besides, I believe my parents
wouldn’t want me to stay sad forever.

556
00:45:38,065 --> 00:45:40,185
Same goes for you too.

557
00:45:42,345 --> 00:45:45,665
No matter what you’ve been through,
or how terrible it was,

558
00:45:46,625 --> 00:45:49,425
in the end, you have to
learn to smile through it.

559
00:46:02,345 --> 00:46:04,665
I just remembered
my favorite childhood memory.

560
00:46:06,345 --> 00:46:11,425
My parents once took me to see
the sea of mist on the mountain.

561
00:46:14,265 --> 00:46:15,585
It was beautiful.

562
00:46:17,225 --> 00:46:22,265
There were flowers and little clouds too.

563
00:46:23,865 --> 00:46:26,625
I still remember that feeling so clearly.

564
00:46:29,465 --> 00:46:35,665
Sea of mist, flowers, little clouds.

565
00:46:39,745 --> 00:46:41,105
Little Cloud Matcha.

566
00:47:27,745 --> 00:47:30,145
It’s as beautiful
as the sea of mist I once saw.

567
00:47:48,385 --> 00:47:49,505
Song.

568
00:47:49,585 --> 00:47:51,345
Did you finish creating
the recipe for Piang?

569
00:47:52,545 --> 00:47:53,425
What’s up?

570
00:47:53,505 --> 00:47:55,265
Do you have any plans tonight?

571
00:47:56,425 --> 00:47:57,785
If not,

572
00:47:58,785 --> 00:47:59,825
want to

573
00:48:01,625 --> 00:48:03,225
go grab some drinks together?

574
00:48:05,585 --> 00:48:07,425
I already made plans with my friends.

575
00:48:08,265 --> 00:48:09,265
How about this?

576
00:48:09,345 --> 00:48:11,065
You can come join us.

577
00:48:11,145 --> 00:48:12,465
My friends are friendly.

578
00:48:12,545 --> 00:48:14,185
I promise it’ll be fun.

579
00:48:15,425 --> 00:48:16,625
Okay.

580
00:48:16,705 --> 00:48:17,665
Let me pack up first.

581
00:48:33,545 --> 00:48:35,465
<i>I’ll send you the location.</i>

582
00:48:56,105 --> 00:48:57,185
Ple.

583
00:48:57,745 --> 00:48:59,985
This is Ploy, my junior teammate.

584
00:49:11,065 --> 00:49:13,745
Nice to meet you, Ple.

585
00:49:18,145 --> 00:49:21,225
Nice to meet you too, Ploy.

586
00:49:50,745 --> 00:49:53,665
Did you forget I'm sitting here too?

587
00:49:55,505 --> 00:49:57,705
Are you jealous, babe?

588
00:49:57,785 --> 00:50:00,865
She’s cute, so I accidentally
fell for her a little.

589
00:50:02,305 --> 00:50:06,145
But you know no one
is more important than you, right babe?

590
00:50:08,945 --> 00:50:11,025
You two are really smooth with this act.

591
00:50:12,545 --> 00:50:15,865
If I didn’t already know,
I’d think you two were actually dating.

592
00:50:18,065 --> 00:50:22,105
And you, want to join in too?

593
00:50:26,465 --> 00:50:28,705
That’s enough. You’re scaring her.

594
00:50:28,785 --> 00:50:30,905
Hey Ploy, weren’t you saying
you wanted to use the restroom?

595
00:50:30,985 --> 00:50:31,865
Go ahead.

596
00:50:31,945 --> 00:50:33,545
I’ll order your drink.

597
00:50:34,305 --> 00:50:35,905
Okay. Thanks.

598
00:50:37,825 --> 00:50:39,545
Why were you teasing her?

599
00:50:40,185 --> 00:50:42,265
Hey, I'll get two of the usual.

600
00:50:43,945 --> 00:50:46,465
Two of the usual, coming right up.

601
00:51:17,025 --> 00:51:17,905
What’s wrong with you?

602
00:51:18,825 --> 00:51:21,705
Ple, as someone
who’s been my friend for a long time,

603
00:51:21,785 --> 00:51:22,785
can you do me a favor?

604
00:51:26,985 --> 00:51:28,185
Kiss me.

605
00:51:28,265 --> 00:51:30,145
Make that woman jealous.

606
00:51:41,825 --> 00:51:42,705
Are you sure?

607
00:52:23,705 --> 00:52:25,585
<i>They’re not really together.</i>

608
00:52:25,665 --> 00:52:26,905
<i>They’re just friends.</i>

609
00:52:51,745 --> 00:52:53,465
That’s Piang.

610
00:52:54,545 --> 00:52:56,505
Why is she drinking so much?

611
00:53:15,825 --> 00:53:16,985
I'm sorry.

612
00:53:20,625 --> 00:53:23,025
Song, you’re here already?

613
00:53:25,105 --> 00:53:26,825
That’s enough. You’re really drunk.

614
00:53:28,705 --> 00:53:30,265
Get up.

615
00:53:32,225 --> 00:53:33,585
No.

616
00:53:35,025 --> 00:53:37,745
I really like you.

617
00:53:38,825 --> 00:53:44,545
Even if you kiss another woman,
it won’t make me like you any less.

618
00:53:46,825 --> 00:53:47,665
Enough.

619
00:53:48,545 --> 00:53:49,985
Why did you get this drunk?

620
00:53:58,425 --> 00:53:59,745
What should we do, Song?

621
00:53:59,825 --> 00:54:01,505
We can’t just leave her like this.

622
00:54:01,585 --> 00:54:02,945
Should we call her a ride home?

623
00:54:04,105 --> 00:54:05,265
We can’t.

624
00:54:06,025 --> 00:54:09,465
She’s the granddaughter of the company
owner where Song and I work.

625
00:54:09,985 --> 00:54:13,745
If something happens to her,
we’ll be in huge trouble.

626
00:54:14,345 --> 00:54:16,065
It’s okay. I’ll handle it myself.

627
00:54:16,785 --> 00:54:18,225
You can get home on your own, right?

628
00:54:19,505 --> 00:54:20,825
Yeah.

629
00:54:20,905 --> 00:54:21,865
What about you, Ple?

630
00:54:21,945 --> 00:54:25,065
I’m a little drunk, but my bodyguard
will take me home. Totally chill.

631
00:54:26,065 --> 00:54:27,465
I’ll take her home myself.

632
00:54:28,065 --> 00:54:29,665
Then I’m counting on you.

633
00:54:29,745 --> 00:54:32,225
-Dance with me first.
-That’s enough.

634
00:54:33,825 --> 00:54:34,665
You don’t have to take me home.

635
00:54:35,865 --> 00:54:37,385
I have to.

636
00:54:37,465 --> 00:54:39,305
I already promised Song.

637
00:54:40,105 --> 00:54:42,745
Besides, there’s something
I want to tell you.

638
00:54:44,305 --> 00:54:45,425
What is it?

639
00:54:47,465 --> 00:54:50,425
I know you two
are usually just teasing each other,

640
00:54:51,385 --> 00:54:52,745
but kissing?

641
00:54:52,825 --> 00:54:54,145
I think that’s a bit too much.

642
00:54:56,385 --> 00:54:57,825
It was just a kiss.

643
00:54:58,345 --> 00:55:00,745
You and I have kissed before too.

644
00:55:02,785 --> 00:55:04,985
So you can do that with just anyone?

645
00:55:06,225 --> 00:55:08,945
I’ve done this
with lots of people already.

646
00:55:09,025 --> 00:55:10,505
I’m just having fun.

647
00:55:10,585 --> 00:55:12,225
I’m not serious about anyone.

648
00:55:14,185 --> 00:55:16,185
But if you can’t accept that,

649
00:55:16,265 --> 00:55:18,305
-I understand--
-Why wouldn’t I accept it?

650
00:55:19,665 --> 00:55:21,225
You’re actually really interesting.

651
00:55:25,705 --> 00:55:27,905
Come on. Let’s go home.

652
00:55:42,625 --> 00:55:43,625
Careful.

653
00:55:47,905 --> 00:55:48,745
Get in properly.

654
00:55:51,265 --> 00:55:54,865
Let’s go dancing again.

655
00:55:54,945 --> 00:55:57,065
What dance? How drunk are you?

656
00:56:16,305 --> 00:56:19,345
So where are we going?

657
00:56:24,265 --> 00:56:25,785
To a hotel.

658
00:57:05,985 --> 00:57:08,745
<i>I’ll do anything to win your heart.</i>

659
00:57:08,825 --> 00:57:10,305
<i>And I’ve already started.</i>

660
00:57:10,385 --> 00:57:12,465
<i>I’ve invested this much in you already.</i>

661
00:57:12,545 --> 00:57:13,865
You should agree to date me.

662
00:57:14,825 --> 00:57:16,305
<i>You even let me come up to your room.</i>

663
00:57:16,385 --> 00:57:17,905
Does that make me special yet?

664
00:57:23,425 --> 00:57:26,025
<i>Didn’t I tell you</i>
<i>to take good care of my granddaughter?</i>

665
00:57:26,105 --> 00:57:28,705
Then why did you let her
disappear all night like this?

666
00:57:28,785 --> 00:57:30,425
Hello, Madam Chairwoman.

667
00:57:30,505 --> 00:57:32,385
Stop getting involved
with my granddaughter.

668
00:59:09,425 --> 00:59:11,945
Subtitle translation by:

